n february  forbes magazine reported that ross has a net worth of  billion he is often called the king of bankruptcy because of his experience in buying bankrupt companies primarily in the manufacturing and steel industries and later selling them for a large profit after operations improve contents  early life  career  rothschild investments  representation of investors in casinos owned by donald trump  establishment of wl ross  co  investments  international steel group isg  international textile group itg  international automotive components group iac  international coal group icg  political activities  political views  organizational memberships and directorships  secretary of commerce  honors  personal life  art collection  references  external links early lifeedit ross was born on november   in weehawken new jersey and grew up in suburban new jersey his father wilbur louis ross sr was a lawyer who later became a judge and his mother agnes née oneill was a school teacher ross drove two hours a day from new jersey to attend the catholic college preparatory xavier high school in manhattan he ran track and was captain of the rifle team he received his bachelors degree from yale college his fathers alma mater at yale ross edited one of the literary magazines and worked at the radio station initially he wanted to be a writer but after his experience in a fiction class requiring  words daily he concluded that he had run out of material his faculty adviser at yale helped him get his first summer job on wall street he earned his mba degree at harvard business school careeredit rothschild investmentsedit in the late s ross began his  year career at the new york city office of n m rothschild  sons where he ran the bankruptcyrestructuring advisory practice representation of investors in casinos owned by donald trumpedit in the s donald trump was in financial trouble because of his casinos in atlantic city his three casinos in atlantic city were under foreclosure threat from lenders ross who was then the senior managing director of rothschild inc represented investors in the casino along with carl icahn ross convinced bondholders to strike a deal with trump that allowed trump to keep control of the casinos establishment of wl ross  coedit in the late s ross started a  million fund at rothschild to invest in distressed assets as the us bubble began to burst he decided he wanted to invest more and advise less in  the yearold banker raised  million to buy out the fund from rothschild and make further investments in distressed assets the new firm was named wl ross  co staff included four top managers who along with ross make up the firms investment committee david h storper who runs trading david l wax a longtime workout specialist stephen j toy an asia expert and pamela k wilson a jp morgan  co veteran wl ross  co was acquired by amvescap now invesco in  in august  ross agreed to reimburse investors  million and pay a fine of  million to settle a securities and exchange commission probe into the overcharging of fees by wl ross  co the company had selfreported the issue to the sec and did not admit any liability investmentsedit international steel group isgedit in  ross founded international steel group after purchasing the assets of several bankrupt steel companies ross had support of the local steelworkers union negotiating a deal with them to save pennsylvanias steel industry leo gerard international president of the united steelworkers union stated about ross that he was open and accessible and candid and honest and he put a lot of money back into the mills so literally tens of thousands of jobs were saved ross sold international steel group to mittal steel company for  billion half in cash and half in stock in april  international textile group itgedit ross combined burlington industries and cone mills in  to form international textile group itg operates five businesses all of which operate under separate brand names cone denim burlington apparel fabrics home furnishings carlisle finishing and nanotex in  ross purchased  of safety components international for  million in  ross merged the firm into his international textile group in february  ross paid  million to settle a lawsuit brought by shareholders that ross breached his fiduciary duty when structuring the merger of two companies that he majorityowned safety components international inc and international textile group inc international textile group was sold to private equity firm platinum equity in  international automotive components group iacedit international automotive components group was formed in  by ross and investment funds managed by franklin mutual advisers in  international automotive components group purchased the european operations of lear corporation in  iac purchased several divisions of collins  aikman in september  investors led by ross made a  million investment in oxford automotive in exchange for approximately  of the company in  oxford merged with wagon automotive international coal group icgedit ross founded the international coal group in  which was formed after several coal companies went bankrupt the united mine workers of america protested the bankruptcy reorganization as it led to changes in health care and pensions for the existing employees the sago mine disaster was a  explosion in a coal mine indirectly owned by international coal group that led to the deaths of  miners federal investigators said a lightning strike was the most likely ignition source for the blast following the disaster the new york posts roddy boyd reported that the mine had  roof collapses in  and that the us department of labor data showed  citations for safety violations in that same period including  times for buildup of toxic gasses miners and their families accused ross of ignoring safety violations ross defended his companys management of the mine arch coal purchased international coal group for  billion in  political activitiesedit ross was raised as a democrat he served under us president bill clinton on the board of the usrussia investment fund later under new york city mayor rudy giuliani ross served as the mayors privatization advisor in january  he put  million in seed money into the campaign of his thenwife betsy mccaughey ross who was seeking the democratic nomination for governor of new york although he was an early supporter of donald trumps presidential campaign ross was previously a registered democrat served as an officer of the new york state democratic party and held fundraisers for democratic candidates at his apartment in new york city since at least  ross has been donating to republican candidates and organizations he became a registered republican in november  political viewsedit on the subject of foreign trade ross has said i am not antitrade i am protrade but im prosensible trade being antitrade is a disadvantage of the american worker and the american manufacturing community ross has also said that the government should provide access to our markets to those countries who play fair play by the rules and give everybody a fair chance to compete those who do not should not get away with it they should be punished initially in favor of the transpacific partnership ross has said that after examining the agreement he found it was not consistent with what was advertised organizational memberships and directorshipsedit ross is a hall of fame member and past director of the turnaround management association since  ross has been the vicechairman of the board of bank of cyprus pcl the largest bank in cyprus as of january  ross was the leader or “grand swipe” of the secret wall street fraternity kappa beta phi he served on the board of trustees of the brookings institution he is also on the board of advisors of yale school of management he donated  million for the construction of evans hall at the yale school of management secretary of commerceedit secretary wilbur ross addresses to employees on march   ross in riyadh saudi arabia may  on november   it was reported by the associated press that ross would be nominated for united states secretary of commerce by incoming president donald trump the trump transition team confirmed trumps intent to nominate him on november   on february   ross was confirmed by the united states senate in a – vote in may  ross accompanied trump on his first foreign visit to saudi arabia in an interview on cnbc ross said there was not a single hint of a protester anywhere there during the whole time we were there saudi arabia banned protesting after the  arab spring and dissenters face the death penalty in  ross said that agreeing to a trade deal with the united kingdom was a low priority for the trump administration honorsedit in  ross was awarded the order of industrial service merit medal by south koreas president kim dae jung for his assistance during the  korean financial crisis ross began working with ireland and irishamerican causes starting in  with an investment in the struggling bank of ireland in recognition for his efforts on november   ross was awarded the american irish historical society gold medal at the waldorf astoria hotel new york the medal is awarded to individuals who make an especially meritorious contribution to irish american life ross was awarded the medal of the order of the rising sun gold and silver star by japanese ambassador sumio kusaka on behalf of the japanese government at kusakas new york residence on february   this was in recognition for strengthening the bonds between japan and the usa including his service as chairman of the board of new yorks japan society which had begun in  after being on its board of directors since  his work to promote and strengthen the japanese economy and his relief efforts after the  tōhoku earthquake and tsunami personal lifeedit ross married judith nodine in  they divorced in  together they had two children jessica and amanada in  he married his second wife new york lt governor betsy mccaughey they divorced in  on october   ross married his third wife hilary geary a society writer for quest magazine art collectionedit ross owns an art collection valued at  million that includes pieces ranging from western surrealists to contemporary eastern sculptures ross owns  works by rené magritte valued at  million including some of the artists most valuable paintings such as the pilgrim referencesedit  a b wilbur ross jr forbescom retrieved    boak josh november   trump taps billionaire investor ross for commerce secretary associated press retrieved  november    zarroli jim november   trump taps billionaire investor wilbur ross for commerce secretary npr retrieved november     egan matt  wilbur ross approved by senate as trumps commerce secretary cnnmoney retrieved    john parkinson january   king of bankruptcy wilbur ross grilled on trade climate change and infrastructure during confirmation hearing abc news   a b c d e f gross daniel  november  the bottom feeder king new york magazine    archived from the original on  november  retrieved  november    a b c d byrnes nanette is wilbur ross crazy december   bloomberg business week   a b c what you need to know about commerce secretary pick wilbur ross trumps billionaire pal fortune magazine november     collins jc how rothschild inc saved donald trump philosophyofmetricscom philosophy of metrics retrieved  november    benner katie wilbur ross sells out the street retrieved october     josh kosman august   sec slaps wilbur ross for misallocating fees the new york post   arnold chris december   wilbur ross the best commerce secretary pick dems could hope for npr   kosman josh october   wilbur ross sells out the new york post   wilbur ross buys  of safety components international from zapata corp for  million press release prnewswire september     international textile group inc and safety components international inc announce agreement to combine press release prnewswire augu